GENERATE the real file caddy/admin.hash (gitignored) — do not copy this one.
It must contain ONLY the bcrypt hash on a single line. Generate it with:

  make hash            # prompts for the password (keeps it out of shell history)

Avoid putting the plaintext on the command line (e.g. `caddy hash-password --plaintext 'pw'`)
— it leaks into shell history and the process list. `make hash` passes it via an env var instead.

Example of what the generated file looks like (do NOT use this value):
$2a$14$bPUVyCTBKu022eWbulixWeX0TlpscswPMmeao7WtjjsDy8/alD1E.
